<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Gas fireplace won&rsquo;t light &mdash; thermopile is the most common cause and it&rsquo;s a straightforward repair</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>The most common gas fireplace call in Los Angeles is a unit that won&rsquo;t light or won&rsquo;t stay lit. In the majority of cases this is a thermopile or thermocouple failure &mdash; small components that generate the millivolt signal to open the gas valve. These are inexpensive parts and a straightforward repair. Flat-rate pricing that assumes a gas valve replacement costs you significantly more than the actual fix.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full assessment including a millivolt reading on the thermopile to confirm exactly which component failed. After diagnosis you get two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part. Gas fireplace calls include supply pressure verification, leak test after any gas component work, and confirming safe operation before we leave.</p>
      <p>Outdoor fireplaces and fire pits are a significant part of our LA fireplace work. Coastal properties in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach deal with accelerated corrosion from salt air &mdash; burner components, igniter wires, and valve assemblies corrode faster than manufacturer specifications assume. We assess coastal units for corrosion as part of every outdoor fireplace service call.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128293; Gas fireplaces</h3>
        <p>Built-in and insert units. Thermopile, thermocouple, igniter, gas valve, burner assembly. Gas supply check and leak test included on every call. Most common repair in LA.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#9889; Electric fireplaces</h3>
        <p>Heating element, blower motor, LED flame effect, remote/control board. Simpler than gas &mdash; no gas safety requirements. Often the lowest-cost fireplace repairs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#127774; Outdoor / fire pits</h3>
        <p>Gas fire pits, fire tables, outdoor fireplaces. Coastal salt air corrosion is a primary concern in LA. Burner cleaning and igniter replacement are the most common outdoor calls.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="safety-block">
      <div class="safety-label">&#9888; Gas fireplace safety &mdash; what to do if you smell gas</div>
      <p>If you smell gas near your fireplace: do not operate any switches or electronics, do not use your phone near the unit, leave the room and ventilate if safe, then call SoCalGas (1-800-427-2200) from outside. After the gas company clears the area, call us for diagnosis and repair. We check for gas leaks on every fireplace service call before and after any work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Labor Rates by Repair Type &mdash; Los Angeles 2026</p>
    <h2>What fireplace repair labor costs in Los Angeles</h2>
