    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about fireplace repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does gas fireplace repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor runs $150&ndash;$380 for standard gas fireplaces. Thermopile and igniter repairs &mdash; the most common calls &mdash; run $150&ndash;$300. Parts are quoted separately. Gas valve replacement runs $250&ndash;$420 in labor. The $89 diagnostic fee applies when you approve the repair.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">My gas fireplace won&rsquo;t stay lit. What is it?</div><div class="faq-a">A fireplace that lights then goes out within 30&ndash;90 seconds is almost always a thermopile with low millivolt output. The thermopile doesn&rsquo;t generate enough signal to hold the gas valve open. We test thermopile output before recommending any part. A new thermopile plus labor typically totals $150&ndash;$250.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do you repair outdoor fire pits in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. We service outdoor gas fireplaces, fire pits, and fire tables throughout Los Angeles. Coastal units in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach face accelerated corrosion from salt air. We assess outdoor units for corrosion as part of every service call.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why won&rsquo;t my fireplace light after not using it all summer?</div><div class="faq-a">LA fireplaces unused over summer frequently have spider or insect nests in the burner orifices and pilot tube. This is the most common &ldquo;won&rsquo;t light&rdquo; call after Labor Day. Cleaning resolves it with no parts needed. The Studio City example above came in at $86 total.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. Parts quoted separately after diagnosis. Gas calls include supply pressure check and post-repair leak test at no extra charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem, including thermopile millivolt testing and gas supply pressure check. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What warranty do you provide on fireplace repair?</div><div class="faq-a">90 days on parts and labor. Same issue within 90 days &mdash; we come back at no charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
